sendVIMS - simple VeeJay VIMS client for Pure Data
        (C) 2002-2004 Niels Elburg <elburg@hio.hen.nl>
        (C) 2004 Tom Schouten <doelie@zzz.kotnet.org>

This is free software covered under the GNU GPL. See COPYING for details.

Requirements
------------
- Pure Data development headers
- pthreads
- a matching VeeJay backend vims.h

Regenerating aliases
--------------------
Copy the current backend header first:

    cp /path/to/veejaycore/vims.h .
    ./parse-vims.pl vims.h > selectors.h

selectors.h contains Pd aliases for supported fire-and-forget VIMS events plus
common live-use shortcuts. Canonical aliases are generated by lowercasing VIMS_*
names and replacing underscores with dots:

    VIMS_VIDEO_PLAY_FORWARD -> video.play.forward
    VIMS_AUDIO_BEAT_TOGGLE  -> audio.beat.toggle

The object also accepts raw VIMS ports as pNNN messages for supported event
ports only:

    [p010(     same as [video.play.forward( and [play(

VIMS ids 400..499 are intentionally not exposed. Those commands return
variable payloads on the command socket, such as sample lists, stream lists,
images, keyframes, chain dumps, and VIMS lists. sendVIMS does not parse command
socket replies. It only sends events and consumes the periodic status socket.
Raw p400..p499 messages are blocked for the same reason.

Building and installing
-----------------------

    ./configure --prefix=/usr/local
    make
    sudo make install

Installed files:

    <prefix>/lib/pd/extra/sendVIMS.pd_linux
    <prefix>/lib/pd/doc/5.reference/help-sendVIMS.pd

Running
-------
Start veejay first, for example:

    veejay -p 3490 video.avi

Then start Pd with the external path:

    pd -path /usr/local/lib/pd/extra

Create the object:

    [sendVIMS localhost 3490]

Useful messages:

    [connect localhost 3490(
    [disconnect(
    [reconnect(
    [aliases(      prints supported Pd aliases
    [commands(     same as aliases
    [play(
    [stop(
    [speed 2(
    [frame 1000(
    [sample 3(
    [beat.toggle(
    [sync.mode 3(
    [mix.crossfade 50(

Status output
-------------
The outlet emits one Pd list per backend status packet. Current VeeJay status is
133 floats indexed 0..132. Use [list length] and [list split] instead of a giant
[unpack]. Open help-sendVIMS.pd for the full per-token status map, live list-split examples, and VIMS command argument docs harvested from vj-eventman.c.

Protocol model
--------------
sendVIMS deliberately has a small protocol model:

    Pd -> VeeJay: fire-and-forget VIMS events
    VeeJay -> Pd: periodic 133-float status list

It does not implement the GUI reply protocol on the command socket. Keep list,
image, query, and getter commands in a GUI client, not in this Pd external.
